  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-23 21:43 UTC \u2014 [P4: Alpha Research] Integrate the Ledger Health Check Into the Overnight Runner and Fix the Live Wrapper Seam So the Pipeline Checks Its Own History at Production Time\n\n**Task:** Update the overnight runner to execute the ledger-health validator after append, then validate the full path end to end and fix any wrapper issues revealed by live execution.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- Updated runner:\n  - `/home/ubuntu/clawd/scripts/run_overnight_monitoring.sh`\n- Runner order is now:\n  1. write latest metrics\n  2. append history\n  3. validate ledger health\n  4. render compact comparison\n- Initial live validation exposed a shell quoting / wrapper seam.\n- Fixed the wrapper and reran the end-to-end path.\n- Wrote integration artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v13c-ledger-health-check-integrated-live.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nI\u2019m glad we forced a real run here, because this is exactly where small shell mistakes show up. The integration itself is still the right design, and fixing the wrapper immediately is much better than leaving a latent bug waiting for scheduled execution later.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep the ledger-health validator integrated into the runner.\n- Treat the runner as a self-checking pipeline component, not just a launcher.\n\n**Next:** On the next P4 heartbeat, confirm the corrected runner output cleanly captures both validation and comparison output in a stable order.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-23 21:39 UTC \u2014 [P3: Strategy Development] Decide Whether the Overnight Ledger Health Check Should Stay Manual or Be Integrated Into the Runner Where the Data Is Actually Produced\n\n**Task:** Make the operational decision on whether the new ledger-health validator should remain a manual maintenance tool or become part of the overnight runner path as an automatic post-append integrity check.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- Decision: **integrate the ledger-health check into the runner path**.\n- Reasoning:\n  - health is most valuable immediately after append\n  - failure detection is better at production time than as a later manual step\n  - self-checking pipelines are safer than pipelines that depend on humans remembering validation\n- Wrote integration-decision artifact: `/home/ubuntu/clawd/patches/v13b-ledger-health-check-integration-decision.spec.md`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is the right move. A ledger validator that only runs when someone remembers to call it is useful, but not nearly as useful as a pipeline that checks its own output while it\u2019s still warm. As long as the validator stays small and deterministic, it belongs in the runner.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Fold the ledger-health check into the overnight runner.\n- Keep the validator narrow so it doesn\u2019t become an unreliable source of noise.\n\n**Next:** On the next P3 heartbeat, update the runner to execute the health check after append and validate the full path end to end.\n\n---\n## 2026-0",
